article.headline: Cent. Michigan 65, Toledo 52
article.story: MOUNT PLEASANT, Mich. -- Trey Zeigler scored 30 points, including making five 3-pointers, as Central Michigan beat Toledo 65-52 on Wednesday night. Zeigler shot 12 for 21 from the field, taking 11 tries from long distance, as the Chippewas (4-11, 1-1 Mid-American) ended a two-game skid. Jalin Thomas helped out with a double-double for Central Michigan, scoring 15 points and pulling down 11 rebounds. Reese Holliday led the Rockets (3-13, 0-2) with 14 points, including shooting 6 of 9 from the free throw line. Anthony Wright added 12 points for Toledo. The Chippewas shot 48.1 percent from the field while the Rockets shot 34.9 percent.
